37namespace {
38// Max number of frames the buffer will hold.
39constexpr size_t kMaxFramesBuffered = 800;
40
41// Max number of decoded frame info that will be saved.
42constexpr int kMaxFramesHistory = 1 << 13;
43
44// The time it's allowed for a frame to be late to its rendering prediction and
45// still be rendered.
46constexpr int kMaxAllowedFrameDelayMs = 5;
47
48constexpr int64_t kLogNonDecodedIntervalMs = 5000;
49} // namespace
50
51FrameBuffer::FrameBuffer(Clock* clock,
52 VCMTiming* timing,
53 VCMReceiveStatisticsCallback* stats_callback)
54 : decoded_frames_history_(kMaxFramesHistory),
55 clock_(clock),
56 callback_queue_(nullptr),
57 jitter_estimator_(clock),
58 timing_(timing),
59 inter_frame_delay_(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds()),
60 stopped_(false),
61 protection_mode_(kProtectionNack),
62 stats_callback_(stats_callback),
63 last_log_non_decoded_ms_(-kLogNonDecodedIntervalMs),
64 add_rtt_to_playout_delay_(
65 webrtc::field_trial::IsEnabled("WebRTC-AddRttToPlayoutDelay")),
66 rtt_mult_settings_(RttMultExperiment::GetRttMultValue()) {
67 callback_checker_.Detach();
68}
69
70FrameBuffer::~FrameBuffer() {
71 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&construction_checker_);
72}

74void FrameBuffer::NextFrame(
75 int64_t max_wait_time_ms,
76 bool keyframe_required,
77 rtc::TaskQueue* callback_queue,
78 std::function<void(std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame>, ReturnReason)> handler) {
79 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&callback_checker_);
80 RTC_DCHECK(callback_queue->IsCurrent());
81 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "FrameBuffer::NextFrame");
82 int64_t latest_return_time_ms =
83 clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() + max_wait_time_ms;
84
85 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
86 if (stopped_) {
87 return;
88 }
89 latest_return_time_ms_ = latest_return_time_ms;
90 keyframe_required_ = keyframe_required;
91 frame_handler_ = handler;
92 callback_queue_ = callback_queue;
93 StartWaitForNextFrameOnQueue();
94}
95
96void FrameBuffer::StartWaitForNextFrameOnQueue() {
97 RTC_DCHECK(callback_queue_);
98 RTC_DCHECK(!callback_task_.Running());
99 int64_t wait_ms = FindNextFrame(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
100 callback_task_ = RepeatingTaskHandle::DelayedStart(
101 callback_queue_->Get(), TimeDelta::Millis(wait_ms), [this] {
102 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&callback_checker_);
103 // If this task has not been cancelled, we did not get any new frames
104 // while waiting. Continue with frame delivery.
105 std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame;
106 std::function<void(std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame>, ReturnReason)>
107 frame_handler;
108 {
109 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
110 if (!frames_to_decode_.empty()) {
111 // We have frames, deliver!
112 frame = absl::WrapUnique(GetNextFrame());
113 } else if (clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() < latest_return_time_ms_) {
114 // If there's no frames to decode and there is still time left, it
115 // means that the frame buffer was cleared between creation and
116 // execution of this task. Continue waiting for the remaining time.
117 int64_t wait_ms = FindNextFrame(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
118 return TimeDelta::Millis(wait_ms);
119 }
120 frame_handler = std::move(frame_handler_);
121 CancelCallback();
122 }
123 // Deliver frame, if any. Otherwise signal timeout.
124 ReturnReason reason = frame ? kFrameFound : kTimeout;
125 frame_handler(std::move(frame), reason);
126 return TimeDelta::Zero(); // Ignored.
127 });
128}
129
130int64_t FrameBuffer::FindNextFrame(int64_t now_ms) {
131 int64_t wait_ms = latest_return_time_ms_ - now_ms;
132 frames_to_decode_.clear();
133
134 // |last_continuous_frame_| may be empty below, but nullopt is smaller
135 // than everything else and loop will immediately terminate as expected.
136 for (auto frame_it = frames_.begin();
137 frame_it != frames_.end() && frame_it->first <= last_continuous_frame_;
138 ++frame_it) {
139 if (!frame_it->second.continuous ||
140 frame_it->second.num_missing_decodable > 0) {
141 continue;
142 }
143
144 EncodedFrame* frame = frame_it->second.frame.get();
145
146 if (keyframe_required_ && !frame->is_keyframe())
147 continue;
148
149 auto last_decoded_frame_timestamp =
150 decoded_frames_history_.GetLastDecodedFrameTimestamp();
151
152 // TODO(https://bugs.webrtc.org/9974): consider removing this check
153 // as it may make a stream undecodable after a very long delay between
154 // frames.
155 if (last_decoded_frame_timestamp &&
156 AheadOf(*last_decoded_frame_timestamp, frame->Timestamp())) {
157 continue;
158 }
159
160 // Gather all remaining frames for the same superframe.
161 std::vector<FrameMap::iterator> current_superframe;
162 current_superframe.push_back(frame_it);
163 bool last_layer_completed = frame_it->second.frame->is_last_spatial_layer;
164 FrameMap::iterator next_frame_it = frame_it;
165 while (!last_layer_completed) {
166 ++next_frame_it;
167
168 if (next_frame_it == frames_.end() || !next_frame_it->second.frame) {
169 break;
170 }
171
172 if (next_frame_it->second.frame->Timestamp() != frame->Timestamp() ||
173 !next_frame_it->second.continuous) {
174 break;
175 }
176
177 if (next_frame_it->second.num_missing_decodable > 0) {
178 bool has_inter_layer_dependency = false;
179 for (size_t i = 0; i < EncodedFrame::kMaxFrameReferences &&
180 i < next_frame_it->second.frame->num_references;
181 ++i) {
182 if (next_frame_it->second.frame->references[i] >= frame_it->first) {
183 has_inter_layer_dependency = true;
184 break;
185 }
186 }
187
188 // If the frame has an undecoded dependency that is not within the same
189 // temporal unit then this frame is not yet ready to be decoded. If it
190 // is within the same temporal unit then the not yet decoded dependency
191 // is just a lower spatial frame, which is ok.
192 if (!has_inter_layer_dependency ||
193 next_frame_it->second.num_missing_decodable > 1) {
194 break;
195 }
196 }
197
198 current_superframe.push_back(next_frame_it);
199 last_layer_completed = next_frame_it->second.frame->is_last_spatial_layer;
200 }
201 // Check if the current superframe is complete.
202 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10064): consider returning all available to
203 // decode frames even if the superframe is not complete yet.
204 if (!last_layer_completed) {
205 continue;
206 }
207
208 frames_to_decode_ = std::move(current_superframe);
209
210 if (frame->RenderTime() == -1) {
211 frame->SetRenderTime(timing_->RenderTimeMs(frame->Timestamp(), now_ms));
212 }
213 wait_ms = timing_->MaxWaitingTime(frame->RenderTime(), now_ms);
214
215 // This will cause the frame buffer to prefer high framerate rather
216 // than high resolution in the case of the decoder not decoding fast
217 // enough and the stream has multiple spatial and temporal layers.
218 // For multiple temporal layers it may cause non-base layer frames to be
219 // skipped if they are late.
220 if (wait_ms < -kMaxAllowedFrameDelayMs)
221 continue;
222
223 break;
224 }
225 wait_ms = std::min<int64_t>(wait_ms, latest_return_time_ms_ - now_ms);
226 wait_ms = std::max<int64_t>(wait_ms, 0);
227 return wait_ms;
228}
229
230EncodedFrame* FrameBuffer::GetNextFrame() {
231 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&callback_checker_);
232 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
233 // TODO(ilnik): remove |frames_out| use frames_to_decode_ directly.
234 std::vector<EncodedFrame*> frames_out;
235
236 RTC_DCHECK(!frames_to_decode_.empty());
237 bool superframe_delayed_by_retransmission = false;
238 size_t superframe_size = 0;
239 EncodedFrame* first_frame = frames_to_decode_[0]->second.frame.get();
240 int64_t render_time_ms = first_frame->RenderTime();
241 int64_t receive_time_ms = first_frame->ReceivedTime();
242 // Gracefully handle bad RTP timestamps and render time issues.
243 if (HasBadRenderTiming(*first_frame, now_ms)) {
244 jitter_estimator_.Reset();
245 timing_->Reset();
246 render_time_ms = timing_->RenderTimeMs(first_frame->Timestamp(), now_ms);
247 }
248
249 for (FrameMap::iterator& frame_it : frames_to_decode_) {
250 RTC_DCHECK(frame_it != frames_.end());
251 EncodedFrame* frame = frame_it->second.frame.release();
252
253 frame->SetRenderTime(render_time_ms);
254
255 superframe_delayed_by_retransmission |= frame->delayed_by_retransmission();
256 receive_time_ms = std::max(receive_time_ms, frame->ReceivedTime());
257 superframe_size += frame->size();
258
259 PropagateDecodability(frame_it->second);
260 decoded_frames_history_.InsertDecoded(frame_it->first, frame->Timestamp());
261
262 // Remove decoded frame and all undecoded frames before it.
263 if (stats_callback_) {
264 unsigned int dropped_frames =
265 std::count_if(frames_.begin(), frame_it,
266 [](const std::pair<const int64_t, FrameInfo>& frame) {
267 return frame.second.frame != nullptr;
268 });
269 if (dropped_frames > 0) {
270 stats_callback_->OnDroppedFrames(dropped_frames);
271 }
272 }
273
274 frames_.erase(frames_.begin(), ++frame_it);
275
276 frames_out.push_back(frame);
277 }
278
279 if (!superframe_delayed_by_retransmission) {
280 int64_t frame_delay;
281
282 if (inter_frame_delay_.CalculateDelay(first_frame->Timestamp(),
283 &frame_delay, receive_time_ms)) {
284 jitter_estimator_.UpdateEstimate(frame_delay, superframe_size);
285 }
286
287 float rtt_mult = protection_mode_ == kProtectionNackFEC ? 0.0 : 1.0;
288 absl::optional<float> rtt_mult_add_cap_ms = absl::nullopt;
289 if (rtt_mult_settings_.has_value()) {
290 rtt_mult = rtt_mult_settings_->rtt_mult_setting;
291 rtt_mult_add_cap_ms = rtt_mult_settings_->rtt_mult_add_cap_ms;
292 }
293 timing_->SetJitterDelay(
294 jitter_estimator_.GetJitterEstimate(rtt_mult, rtt_mult_add_cap_ms));
295 timing_->UpdateCurrentDelay(render_time_ms, now_ms);
296 } else {
297 if (RttMultExperiment::RttMultEnabled() || add_rtt_to_playout_delay_)
298 jitter_estimator_.FrameNacked();
299 }
300
301 UpdateJitterDelay();
302 UpdateTimingFrameInfo();
303
304 if (frames_out.size() == 1) {
305 return frames_out[0];
306 } else {
307 return CombineAndDeleteFrames(frames_out);
308 }
309}
310
311bool FrameBuffer::HasBadRenderTiming(const EncodedFrame& frame,
312 int64_t now_ms) {
313 // Assume that render timing errors are due to changes in the video stream.
314 int64_t render_time_ms = frame.RenderTimeMs();
315 // Zero render time means render immediately.
316 if (render_time_ms == 0) {
317 return false;
318 }
319 if (render_time_ms < 0) {
320 return true;
321 }
322 const int64_t kMaxVideoDelayMs = 10000;
323 if (std::abs(render_time_ms - now_ms) > kMaxVideoDelayMs) {
324 int frame_delay = static_cast<int>(std::abs(render_time_ms - now_ms));
325 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
326 << "A frame about to be decoded is out of the configured "
327 "delay bounds ("
328 << frame_delay << " > " << kMaxVideoDelayMs
329 << "). Resetting the video jitter buffer.";
330 return true;
331 }
332 if (static_cast<int>(timing_->TargetVideoDelay()) > kMaxVideoDelayMs) {
333 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "The video target delay has grown larger than "
334 << kMaxVideoDelayMs << " ms.";
335 return true;
336 }
337 return false;
338}

346void FrameBuffer::Stop() {
347 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "FrameBuffer::Stop");
348 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
349 if (stopped_)
350 return;
351 stopped_ = true;
352
353 CancelCallback();
354}

371bool FrameBuffer::ValidReferences(const EncodedFrame& frame) const {
372 for (size_t i = 0; i < frame.num_references; ++i) {
373 if (frame.references[i] >= frame.Id())
374 return false;
375
376 for (size_t j = i + 1; j < frame.num_references; ++j) {
377 if (frame.references[i] == frame.references[j])
378 return false;
379 }
380 }
381
382 return true;
383}
384
385void FrameBuffer::CancelCallback() {
386 // Called from the callback queue or from within Stop().
387 frame_handler_ = {};
388 callback_task_.Stop();
389 callback_queue_ = nullptr;
390 callback_checker_.Detach();
391}

393int64_t FrameBuffer::InsertFrame(std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame) {
394 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "FrameBuffer::InsertFrame");
395 RTC_DCHECK(frame);
396
397 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
398
399 int64_t last_continuous_frame_id = last_continuous_frame_.value_or(-1);
400
401 if (!ValidReferences(*frame)) {
402 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Frame " << frame->Id()
403 << " has invalid frame references, dropping frame.";
404 return last_continuous_frame_id;
405 }
406
407 if (frames_.size() >= kMaxFramesBuffered) {
408 if (frame->is_keyframe()) {
409 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Inserting keyframe " << frame->Id()
410 << " but buffer is full, clearing"
411 " buffer and inserting the frame.";
412 ClearFramesAndHistory();
413 } else {
414 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Frame " << frame->Id()
415 << " could not be inserted due to the frame "
416 "buffer being full, dropping frame.";
417 return last_continuous_frame_id;
418 }
419 }
420
421 auto last_decoded_frame = decoded_frames_history_.GetLastDecodedFrameId();
422 auto last_decoded_frame_timestamp =
423 decoded_frames_history_.GetLastDecodedFrameTimestamp();
424 if (last_decoded_frame && frame->Id() <= *last_decoded_frame) {
425 if (AheadOf(frame->Timestamp(), *last_decoded_frame_timestamp) &&
426 frame->is_keyframe()) {
427 // If this frame has a newer timestamp but an earlier frame id then we
428 // assume there has been a jump in the frame id due to some encoder
429 // reconfiguration or some other reason. Even though this is not according
430 // to spec we can still continue to decode from this frame if it is a
431 // keyframe.
432 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
433 << "A jump in frame id was detected, clearing buffer.";
434 ClearFramesAndHistory();
435 last_continuous_frame_id = -1;
436 } else {
437 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Frame " << frame->Id() << " inserted after frame "
438 << *last_decoded_frame
439 << " was handed off for decoding, dropping frame.";
440 return last_continuous_frame_id;
441 }
442 }
443
444 // Test if inserting this frame would cause the order of the frames to become
445 // ambiguous (covering more than half the interval of 2^16). This can happen
446 // when the frame id make large jumps mid stream.
447 if (!frames_.empty() && frame->Id() < frames_.begin()->first &&
448 frames_.rbegin()->first < frame->Id()) {
449 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "A jump in frame id was detected, clearing buffer.";
450 ClearFramesAndHistory();
451 last_continuous_frame_id = -1;
452 }
453
454 auto info = frames_.emplace(frame->Id(), FrameInfo()).first;
455
456 if (info->second.frame) {
457 return last_continuous_frame_id;
458 }
459
460 if (!UpdateFrameInfoWithIncomingFrame(*frame, info))
461 return last_continuous_frame_id;
462
463 if (!frame->delayed_by_retransmission())
464 timing_->IncomingTimestamp(frame->Timestamp(), frame->ReceivedTime());
465
466 // It can happen that a frame will be reported as fully received even if a
467 // lower spatial layer frame is missing.
468 if (stats_callback_ && frame->is_last_spatial_layer) {
469 stats_callback_->OnCompleteFrame(frame->is_keyframe(), frame->size(),
470 frame->contentType());
471 }
472
473 info->second.frame = std::move(frame);
474
475 if (info->second.num_missing_continuous == 0) {
476 info->second.continuous = true;
477 PropagateContinuity(info);
478 last_continuous_frame_id = *last_continuous_frame_;
479
480 // Since we now have new continuous frames there might be a better frame
481 // to return from NextFrame.
482 if (callback_queue_) {
483 callback_queue_->PostTask([this] {
484 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
485 if (!callback_task_.Running())
486 return;
487 RTC_CHECK(frame_handler_);
488 callback_task_.Stop();
489 StartWaitForNextFrameOnQueue();
490 });
491 }
492 }
493
494 return last_continuous_frame_id;
495}
496
497void FrameBuffer::PropagateContinuity(FrameMap::iterator start) {
498 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "FrameBuffer::PropagateContinuity");
499 RTC_DCHECK(start->second.continuous);
500
501 std::queue<FrameMap::iterator> continuous_frames;
502 continuous_frames.push(start);
503
504 // A simple BFS to traverse continuous frames.
505 while (!continuous_frames.empty()) {
506 auto frame = continuous_frames.front();
507 continuous_frames.pop();
508
509 if (!last_continuous_frame_ || *last_continuous_frame_ < frame->first) {
510 last_continuous_frame_ = frame->first;
511 }
512
513 // Loop through all dependent frames, and if that frame no longer has
514 // any unfulfilled dependencies then that frame is continuous as well.
515 for (size_t d = 0; d < frame->second.dependent_frames.size(); ++d) {
516 auto frame_ref = frames_.find(frame->second.dependent_frames[d]);
517 RTC_DCHECK(frame_ref != frames_.end());
518
519 // TODO(philipel): Look into why we've seen this happen.
520 if (frame_ref != frames_.end()) {
521 --frame_ref->second.num_missing_continuous;
522 if (frame_ref->second.num_missing_continuous == 0) {
523 frame_ref->second.continuous = true;
524 continuous_frames.push(frame_ref);
525 }
526 }
527 }
528 }
529}
530
531void FrameBuffer::PropagateDecodability(const FrameInfo& info) {
532 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "FrameBuffer::PropagateDecodability");
533 for (size_t d = 0; d < info.dependent_frames.size(); ++d) {
534 auto ref_info = frames_.find(info.dependent_frames[d]);
535 RTC_DCHECK(ref_info != frames_.end());
536 // TODO(philipel): Look into why we've seen this happen.
537 if (ref_info != frames_.end()) {
538 RTC_DCHECK_GT(ref_info->second.num_missing_decodable, 0U);
539 --ref_info->second.num_missing_decodable;
540 }
541 }
542}
543
544bool FrameBuffer::UpdateFrameInfoWithIncomingFrame(const EncodedFrame& frame,
545 FrameMap::iterator info) {
546 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "FrameBuffer::UpdateFrameInfoWithIncomingFrame");
547 auto last_decoded_frame = decoded_frames_history_.GetLastDecodedFrameId();
548 RTC_DCHECK(!last_decoded_frame || *last_decoded_frame < info->first);
549
550 // In this function we determine how many missing dependencies this |frame|
551 // has to become continuous/decodable. If a frame that this |frame| depend
552 // on has already been decoded then we can ignore that dependency since it has
553 // already been fulfilled.
554 //
555 // For all other frames we will register a backwards reference to this |frame|
556 // so that |num_missing_continuous| and |num_missing_decodable| can be
557 // decremented as frames become continuous/are decoded.
558 struct Dependency {
559 int64_t frame_id;
560 bool continuous;
561 };
562 std::vector<Dependency> not_yet_fulfilled_dependencies;
563
564 // Find all dependencies that have not yet been fulfilled.
565 for (size_t i = 0; i < frame.num_references; ++i) {
566 // Does |frame| depend on a frame earlier than the last decoded one?
567 if (last_decoded_frame && frame.references[i] <= *last_decoded_frame) {
568 // Was that frame decoded? If not, this |frame| will never become
569 // decodable.
570 if (!decoded_frames_history_.WasDecoded(frame.references[i])) {
571 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
572 if (last_log_non_decoded_ms_ + kLogNonDecodedIntervalMs < now_ms) {
573 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
574 << "Frame " << frame.Id()
575 << " depends on a non-decoded frame more previous than the last "
576 "decoded frame, dropping frame.";
577 last_log_non_decoded_ms_ = now_ms;
578 }
579 return false;
580 }
581 } else {
582 auto ref_info = frames_.find(frame.references[i]);
583 bool ref_continuous =
584 ref_info != frames_.end() && ref_info->second.continuous;
585 not_yet_fulfilled_dependencies.push_back(
586 {frame.references[i], ref_continuous});
587 }
588 }
589
590 info->second.num_missing_continuous = not_yet_fulfilled_dependencies.size();
591 info->second.num_missing_decodable = not_yet_fulfilled_dependencies.size();
592
593 for (const Dependency& dep : not_yet_fulfilled_dependencies) {
594 if (dep.continuous)
595 --info->second.num_missing_continuous;
596
597 frames_[dep.frame_id].dependent_frames.push_back(frame.Id());
598 }
599
600 return true;
601}
602
603void FrameBuffer::UpdateJitterDelay() {
604 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "FrameBuffer::UpdateJitterDelay");
605 if (!stats_callback_)
606 return;
607
608 int max_decode_ms;
609 int current_delay_ms;
610 int target_delay_ms;
611 int jitter_buffer_ms;
612 int min_playout_delay_ms;
613 int render_delay_ms;
614 if (timing_->GetTimings(&max_decode_ms, &current_delay_ms, &target_delay_ms,
615 &jitter_buffer_ms, &min_playout_delay_ms,
616 &render_delay_ms)) {
617 stats_callback_->OnFrameBufferTimingsUpdated(
618 max_decode_ms, current_delay_ms, target_delay_ms, jitter_buffer_ms,
619 min_playout_delay_ms, render_delay_ms);
620 }
621}
622
623void FrameBuffer::UpdateTimingFrameInfo() {
624 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "FrameBuffer::UpdateTimingFrameInfo");
625 absl::optional<TimingFrameInfo> info = timing_->GetTimingFrameInfo();
626 if (info && stats_callback_)
627 stats_callback_->OnTimingFrameInfoUpdated(*info);
628}
629
630void FrameBuffer::ClearFramesAndHistory() {
631 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "FrameBuffer::ClearFramesAndHistory");
632 if (stats_callback_) {
633 unsigned int dropped_frames =
634 std::count_if(frames_.begin(), frames_.end(),
635 [](const std::pair<const int64_t, FrameInfo>& frame) {
636 return frame.second.frame != nullptr;
637 });
638 if (dropped_frames > 0) {
639 stats_callback_->OnDroppedFrames(dropped_frames);
640 }
641 }
642 frames_.clear();
643 last_continuous_frame_.reset();
644 frames_to_decode_.clear();
645 decoded_frames_history_.Clear();
646}
647
648// TODO(philipel): Avoid the concatenation of frames here, by replacing
649// NextFrame and GetNextFrame with methods returning multiple frames.
650EncodedFrame* FrameBuffer::CombineAndDeleteFrames(
651 const std::vector<EncodedFrame*>& frames) const {
652 RTC_DCHECK(!frames.empty());
653 EncodedFrame* first_frame = frames[0];
654 EncodedFrame* last_frame = frames.back();
655 size_t total_length = 0;
656 for (size_t i = 0; i < frames.size(); ++i) {
657 total_length += frames[i]->size();
658 }
659 auto encoded_image_buffer = EncodedImageBuffer::Create(total_length);
660 uint8_t* buffer = encoded_image_buffer->data();
661 first_frame->SetSpatialLayerFrameSize(first_frame->SpatialIndex().value_or(0),
662 first_frame->size());
663 memcpy(buffer, first_frame->data(), first_frame->size());
664 buffer += first_frame->size();
665
666 // Spatial index of combined frame is set equal to spatial index of its top
667 // spatial layer.
668 first_frame->SetSpatialIndex(last_frame->SpatialIndex().value_or(0));
669
670 first_frame->video_timing_mutable()->network2_timestamp_ms =
671 last_frame->video_timing().network2_timestamp_ms;
672 first_frame->video_timing_mutable()->receive_finish_ms =
673 last_frame->video_timing().receive_finish_ms;
674
675 // Append all remaining frames to the first one.
676 for (size_t i = 1; i < frames.size(); ++i) {
677 EncodedFrame* next_frame = frames[i];
678 first_frame->SetSpatialLayerFrameSize(
679 next_frame->SpatialIndex().value_or(0), next_frame->size());
680 memcpy(buffer, next_frame->data(), next_frame->size());
681 buffer += next_frame->size();
682 delete next_frame;
683 }
684 first_frame->SetEncodedData(encoded_image_buffer);
685 return first_frame;
686}
687
688FrameBuffer::FrameInfo::FrameInfo() = default;
689FrameBuffer::FrameInfo::FrameInfo(FrameInfo&&) = default;
690FrameBuffer::FrameInfo::~FrameInfo() = default;
